Our Story

K's Cafe was founded in 2011 by Karman Chhatwal, a young man with a passion for food and hospitality. Chhatwal had always dreamed of owning his own cafe, and he finally decided to take the plunge in 2011. He found a small space in a historic building in downtown Lexington, Kentucky, and he set to work transforming it into his dream cafe.

Chhatwal named his cafe after his grandmother, who had always been a source of inspiration and support for him. The cafe's menu features classic American comfort food with a modern twist. The breakfast menu includes favorites like pancakes, waffles, and eggs Benedict, while the lunch menu features sandwiches, salads, and burgers. The cafe also offers a variety of coffee drinks, teas, and smoothies.

K's Cafe quickly became a popular spot in downtown Lexington. The cafe's friendly atmosphere and delicious food made it a favorite for locals and tourists alike. In 2015, Chhatwal expanded the cafe to include a small retail space, where he sells his own line of baked goods and coffee accessories.

Chhatwal is proud of what he has built with K's Cafe, and he is excited to see what the future holds for his business.
